INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `body`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `excerpt`, `tags`, `author`, `featured_image`, `number_of_view`) VALUES
(1, 'WHY COMPANIES COMPLAIN ABOUT DIFFICULTIES TO KEEP EMPLOYEES AND HOW TO SOLVE IT?', 'why-companies-complain-about-difficulties-to-keep-employees-and-how-to-solve-it', '<p>It is very common to see employee choose to quit a job in Malaysia. And of course the number of employees who are thinking about leaving their jobs are much greater. But do you know how serious the whole picture looks like? Take this:&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;70% of employees plan to leave their jobs&rdquo;,</strong>says Randstad on 22 January 2014. That means nearly seven in 10 employees are looking to leave their jobs this year for better careers. The top reasons are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Uncompetitive salary (55%),</li>\r\n	<li>Lack of recognition at the workplace (35%)</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-why-companies-complain-about-difficulties-to-keep-employees-and-how-to-solve-it.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T134715Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=250a21becd94eb7f983e6b94234e3e770d11bfd5e2a06fa816ad4b438a3f132d&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">And &ldquo;lack of trust in senior leaders&rdquo; (21%)a.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-why-companies-complain-about-difficulties-to-keep-employees-and-how-to-solve-it.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T134715Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=250a21becd94eb7f983e6b94234e3e770d11bfd5e2a06fa816ad4b438a3f132d&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">Are you one of them? Are you happy about your job?&nbsp;</a>Actually the majority Malaysian employees are very loyal to their jobs. Besides the income, the equally important facet is the working relationship. That why people say &ldquo;People don&rsquo;t leave the job, they leave the manager&rdquo;. This is from employee&rsquo;s perspective. After many year&rsquo;s business education, we more prefer to autopsy the situation by one statement:&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;So much of what we call management consists in making it difficult for people to work&hellip;Effective leadership is not about making speeches or being liked; leadership is defined by results not attributes&nbsp;</strong>&ldquo; Said by Peter Drucker. From the Randstad, we can tell the key issue behind each major reasons are&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Under-paid&rdquo;, &ldquo;Talent Ignorance&rdquo;&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Lack of Trust&rdquo;.&nbsp;</strong>Basically it is all because of management. If fortunately we were able to put managers in an equal-level debate, they would have a bad day, because I will say:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If the HR manager did the right job, employee should receive suitable rewards, both financially and emotionally.</li>\r\n	<li>Company management level should build up an open environment for talents to shine, and also should have&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-why-companies-complain-about-difficulties-to-keep-employees-and-how-to-solve-it.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T134715Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=250a21becd94eb7f983e6b94234e3e770d11bfd5e2a06fa816ad4b438a3f132d&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">a proper training process to nourish and develop talent.</a></li>\r\n	<li>If HR signed one employee, which means this employee is good enough for his/her position, so senior should be able to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-why-companies-complain-about-difficulties-to-keep-employees-and-how-to-solve-it.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T134715Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=250a21becd94eb7f983e6b94234e3e770d11bfd5e2a06fa816ad4b438a3f132d&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">trust this employee.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>So we can see that there is a management problem, a problem between senior manager and HR manager, a problem of talent recognition and appreciation, and good employee become the victim. So it is save to conclude that the major cause of 70% unstable employees are the managers. Companies and managers are keep complaining about how difficult to keep talent, even find talent. But actually they are the cause. They had talent staff, or they are having talent staffs, but are they able to recognize, to appreciate, to trust, and to rewards? If they are not able to keep employee, how could they even able to keep talents? It looks like I was complaining that I don&rsquo;t have good kitchen knife, before my wife told me I was holding MIYABI. Or like my wife commented a passing Nissan GTR as normal as others because it has just four wheels as others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/img/blog/why_companies_complain_about_difficulties_to_keep_employees_and%20_how_to_solve_it/blind-spot.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is true that the high turnover slacks company&rsquo;s performance, and also interrupt the smoothness of building career profile of each employee. And there is 70% of your employees are thinking about leaving. So HR manager need to work hard enough to find suitable employees, and offer appropriate attention and rewards. At the whole company level, a strategic intelligence management system need to be established, for both short term and long term organization goals. Do you agree or disagree? Please leave your comment.</p>\r\n', '2016-02-14 06:46:37', '2016-02-14 07:30:25', 'It is very common to see employee choose to quit a job in Malaysia. And of course the number of employees who are thinking about leaving their jobs are much greater. But do you know how serious the whole picture looks like? Take this: “70% of employees plan to leave their jobs”,says Randstad on 22 January 2014. That means nearly seven in 10 employees are looking to leave their jobs this year for better careers.', '', 'XREMO', '', 4),
(2, 'When to quit your job and start your own business', 'when-to-quit-your-job-and-start-your-own-business', '<p><strong>Here are four questions to ask yourself before you quit your day job.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dear Annie:&nbsp;</strong>I&rsquo;ve been in my current job for about five years, and not only do I dislike what I&rsquo;m doing, but our department got a new boss a few months ago who drives me crazy. He has no integrity, encourages us to take shortcuts that do a disservice to customers, and second-guesses every decision anyone on my team makes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve always wanted to start my own business, and I think I have a solid idea for a company. The thing is, I read your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-when-to-quit-your-job-and-start-your-own-business.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135049Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=db7d861510391c9680a109120d58a72f1a536ddd7be145759310261cd37074d9&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">column&nbsp;</a>the high rate of failure among startups &mdash; the ones we never hear about &mdash; and I&rsquo;m debating with myself over taking the plunge. How do you know if you&rsquo;re really ready to run your own company? &mdash;&nbsp;<em>Thinking It Over</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dear Thinking:&nbsp;</strong>Good question, especially given&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-when-to-quit-your-job-and-start-your-own-business.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135049Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=db7d861510391c9680a109120d58a72f1a536ddd7be145759310261cd37074d9&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">the current IPO gold rush&nbsp;</a>, which is creating a whole new batch of overnight-millionaire entrepreneurs. Still, your main motivation right now seems to be getting away from your terrible boss, and that sets off some alarm bells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;You never want to start a company as a reaction to a bad situation,&rdquo; says Ashish Toshniwal. &ldquo;You need to have an idea you are really passionate about, or you&rsquo;ll never make it through the first couple of years, which are extremely tough.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Toshniwal has been in your shoes. About six years ago, at 26, he was unhappy in his job as an engineer at Dell. At the same time, he and a friend, then-Yahoo-engineer Sumit Mehra, were building Facebook apps for fun in their spare time. When smartphone technology came along, the pair quit their jobs to launch Y Media Labs, which now develops mobile apps for PayPal, eBay, Bank of America, Symantec, and many others. The company has grown from the two founders to 141 employees, and Toshniwal expects to hire about 80 more staffers by the end of the year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;We were really passionate about this new technology, and we saw an inflection point, where growth was just about to take off,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;Wanting to leave an unchallenging job, or any particular boss, was never the motivation.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It shouldn&rsquo;t be for you, either. &ldquo;You have to start with what your true passion is, and then work backward and find a way to pursue it,&rdquo; says MJ Gottlieb. &ldquo;You might find that&rsquo;s by getting a different job, rather than starting a business.&rdquo; Gottlieb is the author of&nbsp;<em>How to Ruin a Business Without Really Trying&nbsp;</em>, a compendium of 55 mistakes he made while starting and running six successful companies over the past 23 years. &ldquo;Above all, don&rsquo;t quit your job because you believe you have a great idea for a business,&rdquo; he adds. &ldquo;An idea is not enough.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, what is enough, then? Consider your answers to these four questions:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Do you have any evidence that your idea will fly?&nbsp;</strong>Too many entrepreneurs start companies without doing enough research, or asking enough&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-when-to-quit-your-job-and-start-your-own-business.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135049Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=db7d861510391c9680a109120d58a72f1a536ddd7be145759310261cd37074d9&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">hard questions&nbsp;</a>, to make sure their product or service is &ldquo;something that people actually want or need, and that will entice business away from competitors,&rdquo; says Gottlieb. &ldquo;Especially if you hope to attract investors, you need customers and revenues. Nobody funds an idea.&rdquo; One way to try out your business without quitting your day job: Build your company on the side, in your spare time, until you know for sure it can survive in the marketplace.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Are you ready to be flat broke for a couple of years?&nbsp;</strong>Toshniwal and Mehra funded Y Media Labs with their own savings and credit cards, and then took no cash out of the venture for the first two years while they built a solid customer case and refined their mobile-app technology. &ldquo;We lived a very frugal life,&rdquo; says Toshniwal. &ldquo;In fact, we took such a hit financially that we almost gave up.&rdquo; This isn&rsquo;t everyone&rsquo;s cup of tea. Notes Toshniwali, &ldquo;If you work for someone else, you always get paid no matter how the business is doing.&rdquo; Not so with a startup.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Are you good at solving problems and overcoming obstacles on your own?&nbsp;</strong>One thing Toshniwali missed after he left Dell was the enormous corporate support system he had always taken for granted. &ldquo;As an employee, you have access to the company&rsquo;s resources. You can usually assume your manager or someone else will take care of details and problems that get in your way,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;In a brand-new enterprise, it&rsquo;s just you doing everything &mdash; while being under intense pressure to produce results.&rdquo; This is why it&rsquo;s not unusual for exhausted would-be business owners to run back to a cubicle somewhere.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Would you mind giving up a life outside of work?&nbsp;</strong>And, if you have a family, how do they feel about it? &ldquo;As an entrepreneur, you&rsquo;re always on call, including nights, weekends, and holidays,&rdquo; notes Gottlieb. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve had to miss a lot of birthdays and events, and let down a lot of family and friends. At one point, I realized I hadn&rsquo;t taken a vacation in 14 years.&rdquo; In what has to be in the running for Understatement of the Year, Gottlieb adds, &ldquo;The life of an entrepreneur is not in everyone&rsquo;s DNA.&rdquo; Many entrepreneurs &mdash; including those who have real-life, flesh-and-blood spouses or significant others &mdash; say they feel&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-when-to-quit-your-job-and-start-your-own-business.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135049Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=db7d861510391c9680a109120d58a72f1a536ddd7be145759310261cd37074d9&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">married to their companies&nbsp;</a>.\r\n	<p>If your honest answer to all four questions is &ldquo;yes,&rdquo; then go for it. But if any of the four (or more than one) gives you pause, think about looking for a different job &mdash; maybe even inside your current company, but with a better boss &mdash; instead. Good luck.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2016-02-14 06:49:00', '2016-02-19 08:30:09', 'Dear Annie: I’ve been in my current job for about five years, and not only do I dislike what I’m doing, but our department got a new boss a few months ago who drives me crazy. He has no integrity, encourages us to take shortcuts that do a disservice to customers, and second-guesses every decision anyone on my team makes.', '', 'Anne Fisher', '', 4);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `slug`, `body`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `excerpt`, `tags`, `author`, `featured_image`, `number_of_view`) VALUES
(3, '“THERE’S NO SUCH THING AS AN ORIGINAL IDEA” & 9 OTHER LESSONS M’SIAN STARTUPS TAUGHT ME', 'theres-no-such-thing-as-an-original-idea--9-other-lessons-msian-startups-taught-me', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Are you crazy? How&rsquo;re you going to survive without a steady income?&rdquo;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>That was what majority of my family members told me when I told them I wanted to quit my job and do something of my own. Ever since I graduated, I have always worked in a corporate Fast Moving Consumer Goods (FMCG) environment as a marketer. As a typical Gen-Y, I always struggled to stay focused and seeing my colleagues work through the night (even though they have children at home waiting for their return) made me constantly ask myself,&nbsp;<em>&ldquo;Is this what I really want to spend my whole life doing?&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I mean, working in a super fast-paced FMCG environment is fun and there are tons to learn, but I&rsquo;ve always felt like I&rsquo;m a small cog in a giant machine working for a typical corporate. I desperately yearned for something more and despite all the negative feedback that I&rsquo;ve gotten from my family members and peers, I took the leap in May 2015 and resigned without a backup plan, hoping to find freedom with enough savings to keep myself well-fed (I f*cking love food) for about a year and a half.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this day and age, what inspires me the most are the enormous&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-there-no-such-thing-as-an-original-idea-and_9-other-lessons-msian-startups-taught-me.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135245Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=bb57f4cf5b54fc431f298828e3468aaf036699caa675c8cabd39deec3db6f8d2&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">tech startups&nbsp;</a>that have shown the ability to grow at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-there-no-such-thing-as-an-original-idea-and_9-other-lessons-msian-startups-taught-me.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135245Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=bb57f4cf5b54fc431f298828e3468aaf036699caa675c8cabd39deec3db6f8d2&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">lightning speed&nbsp;</a>. I thought that the most logical action forward was to learn how to code!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/img/blog/there_no_such_thing_as_an_original_idea_and_9_other_lessons_msian_startups_taught_me/top-malaysian-ip-startup-scene-south-east-asia-global-entrepeneurship-summit-2013-kuala-lumpur-agen.png\" /><em>Image Credit: http://www.innovationiseverywhere.com</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>So I quickly signed up for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-there-no-such-thing-as-an-original-idea-and_9-other-lessons-msian-startups-taught-me.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135245Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=bb57f4cf5b54fc431f298828e3468aaf036699caa675c8cabd39deec3db6f8d2&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAIZV2KXWN4LIRWHDQ/20160214/ap-southeast-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=Host&amp;x-amz-security-token=AQoDYXdzEFQakAPxCOWTa5/XPgGqdq4iKPRJ8tMrT9kEncvBJWjh2gf43lNGtI%2Bnjoif3tKYDZ9g0ofIB4vOg59iIYiHf3nbdvdu%2BdBbfE6yoXhWZVhCY%2BxeoAX07oTgGCQkSMVXfMxatzGSJtJ7/JVJdUobvjRXsrWv1Hl0kQwoQlII4DwvrynhzL2p17WUPWPaTl/JBtWkbcrBz6oS2w7pAu5XXXfhHX1r8b/joUyi4Cz7oOgI1CA/BxC%2BLVaYE%2B9vRqnIWhr84gKExsMvJF6viij2GZVsAXN01WMnqCYICgktwbM0Y4z2c%2Bxo8p1vwWIiAIAcOlKydrNGEMGcwffVSToQ0xktgyqaEO3KQ%2BOzB6KwOjE0uRPkBackTAyZUxTHRtN/bStjSRqvGzeIOIzOXtJheucv7iOEbSwAgVMdBCLKJ698ugtBri%2BELAd6C6fCHQ/n2HJO7ddRIeUGpJPMCljTSUg81Gbb7T0sMswMb%2BhM6CtmIR5K6rsIaDP1TgDZEOXa2Bg7j%2BuKl3qQ8CZRhm5Nx1pWAHimIO/j/7UF#\">MaGIC&rsquo;s Web Development Bootcamp&nbsp;</a>, a 9-week program that takes you from a person who has absolutely no programming knowledge to a person empowered with coding skills. I thought that even if I do not want to be a developer by profession, I revel at being able to communicate seamlessly with developers that I may someday work with.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It has been almost 1 month after my graduation from the bootcamp, and in retrospect, I have never made a better decision. The bootcamp has empowered me to be able to create&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3-ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/xremo.com.my/blog-article-there-no-such-thing-as-an-original-idea-and_9-other-lessons-msian-startups-taught-me.html?X-Amz-Date=20160214T135245Z&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Signature=bb57f4cf5b54fc